The paper deals with graph spanners, which are a fundamental topic in computer science and graph theory. The paper discusses the limitations of LP relaxations for approximating graph spanners, which is a common technique in optimization algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT) and complexity theory (cs.CC) in proving the integrality gaps.
